# Cursor Rules — Della Sigrest Portfolio

## Project Overview
- **Type:** Static portfolio site (HTML/CSS/JS, no build step)
- **Framework:** Vanilla HTML5, CSS3, ES6+ JavaScript
- **Deployment:** Vercel (della-portfolio.vercel.app)
- **Purpose:** Product designer portfolio showcasing 6 case studies

---

## Design System Reference

### Architecture
All design tokens are in `styles.css` using CSS custom properties (`:root {}`):
- **Colors:** Backgrounds, surfaces, text, borders, accent (teal #2dd4bf)
- **Typography:** Inter font, 4 weight levels, semantic scale
- **Spacing:** Responsive padding (clamp functions), consistent gaps
- **Motion:** 0.25s easing, scroll animations, hover transitions
- **Shadows:** Minimal hierarchy (subtle → elevated)

### Key Files
- `DESIGN.md` — Complete design token documentation (consult before changes)
- `styles.css` — Single source of truth for all visual rules
- `index.html` — Homepage structure
- `case-[name].html` — 6 case study pages
- `about.html` — About page

---

## Code Style & Constraints

### CSS Guidelines
1. **Use CSS variables exclusively** — Never hardcode colors/sizes
   ```css
   /* Good */
   color: var(--text-primary);
   transition: all var(--transition);
   
   /* Avoid */
   color: #e8e8e8;
   transition: all 0.25s;
   ```

2. **Maintain selector specificity** — Keep selectors as simple as possible
   ```css
   /* Good: Direct element + single class */
   .case-card:hover { }
   
   /* Avoid: Deep nesting or combinators */
   .cases > .case-card .case-content .case-title:hover { }
   ```

3. **Responsive design** — Use clamp() for fluid typography; mobile-first media queries
   ```css
   font-size: clamp(14px, 2vw, 16px);
   
   @media (max-width: 768px) {
     /* Changes for tablet */
   }
   ```

4. **Animations** — Always include fallback for prefers-reduced-motion
   ```css
   @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
     * { animation-duration: 0.01ms !important; }
   }
   ```

5. **Accessibility** — Maintain WCAG AA contrast ratios, no color-only information
   ```css
   color-contrast: 4.5:1 minimum for body text
   ```

### HTML Guidelines
1. **Semantic markup** — Use HTML5 elements correctly (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
2. **Class naming** — BEM-inspired, single class per element when possible
   ```html
   <!-- Good -->
   <div class="case-card">
     <div class="case-img">...</div>
     <div class="case-content">...</div>
   </div>
   
   <!-- Avoid -->
   <div class="card card-large card-dark">...</div>
   ```

3. **Data attributes** — For JavaScript hooks (separate from styling)
   ```html
   <button data-action="expand">Show More</button>
   ```

4. **Accessibility attributes** — aria-labels, role attributes where needed

### JavaScript Guidelines
1. **Vanilla JS only** — No frameworks or bundlers
2. **Event delegation** — Attach listeners to parent when managing multiple elements
3. **Performance** — Debounce scroll/resize handlers
4. **Mobile menu** — Toggle `.open` class on `.nav-links` and `.nav-toggle`

---

## Dark Mode & Brand Identity

### Color Palette (Dark Mode Only)
- **Primary background:** `#0b0b0b` (--bg)
- **Surface:** `#131313` (--surface), hover to `#191919`
- **Text:** `#e8e8e8` primary, `#888` secondary, `#555` tertiary
- **Accent:** `#2dd4bf` teal — use for CTAs, highlights, interactive feedback
- **Borders:** `#1e1e1e` default, `#2a2a2a` hover

### Typography
- **Font:** Inter (no fallback needed, already loaded)
- **Hero H1:** clamp(34px, 4.5vw, 52px), weight 700, line-height 1.12
- **Body:** 16px, weight 400, line-height 1.8, color --text-secondary
- **Metadata:** 11-13px, weight 600 or 500, uppercase when semantic

### Motion & Interactions
- **Transitions:** 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) standard
- **Hover states:** Change color, add subtle transform, elevate shadow
- **Scroll animations:** Fade-in + slideY(16px) on entry
- **No autoplay media:** Respect user preferences

---

## Page Structure

### Index (Homepage)
1. **Navigation** — Fixed top nav with links (Home, Work, About)
2. **Hero** — Full-height intro with eyebrow, h1, subtitle, CTA
3. **Pillars** — 2-column grid of skill/approach summaries
4. **Cases** — 6 case cards stacked vertically, hover reveals accent colors
5. **Footer** — Copyright, social links, contact

### Case Study Pages
1. **Hero** — Page-level h1, eyebrow (accent color), subtitle
2. **Meta Grid** — Horizontal display of Role, Timeline, Team, Tools
3. **Body** — Long-form narrative with h2s, p, ul, blockquotes, images
4. **Metrics** — Grid of key numbers (if applicable)
5. **Images** — Full-width or grid layouts with proper aspect ratios
6. **Next Case** — Link to related case study at bottom

### About Page
1. **Hero** — About h1, subtitle
2. **Body** — Paragraphs with optional h2 breaks
3. **Links** — Resume, GitHub, LinkedIn, etc.

