## Integration with Stitch & Claude

### Stitch Workflow
1. Export `DESIGN.md` to Stitch (copy/paste content into Stitch canvas)
2. Stitch generates moodboards, component variations, layout explorations
3. Export updated tokens back to `DESIGN.md`
4. Claude reads updated `DESIGN.md` and implements changes in Cursor

### Claude Code Workflow
1. Claude reads `DESIGN.md` for all token values
2. Claude uses Visual Editor to drag/drop HTML elements
3. CSS updates flow to `styles.css` automatically
4. Claude tests with prefers-reduced-motion, mobile breakpoints, color contrast

### File Handoff
- **From Stitch to Claude:** Updated `DESIGN.md`
- **From Claude to you:** Ready-to-deploy changes in `styles.css`
- **Keep in sync:** Never edit `DESIGN.md` manually; always export from Stitch or document changes

---

## Accessibility & Performance

### WCAG AA Compliance
- Text contrast: 4.5:1 minimum (primary on background)
- Interactive elements: 44×44px minimum touch target
- Color not sole indicator (use text, icons, borders)
- Keyboard navigation functional on all links/buttons
- Focus states visible (use `:focus-visible`)

### Performance Targets
- Page load: < 2s (Vercel CDN optimized)
- Lighthouse: 90+ (Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices)
- Images: Responsive and optimized
- No unused CSS (monolithic styles.css is intentional)
- No JavaScript dependencies (vanilla only)

### Mobile Optimization
- Responsive typography (clamp functions)
- Touch-friendly spacing and targets
- Full-width sections scale to viewport
- Hamburger menu on < 768px
- Test on actual devices (not just browser DevTools)

